      "id": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260510234724.htm",
      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260510234724.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] This 800-year-old Chinese exercise helps lower blood pressure naturally",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.sciencedaily.com&amp;sz=128\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nAn ancient Chinese exercise routine may be just as powerful as a daily brisk walk for lowering blood pressure — without equipment, gyms, or intense workouts. In a major clinical trial, adults with stage 1 hypertension who practiced baduanjin, a gentle mind-body exercise combining slow movements, breathing, and meditation, saw meaningful drops in blood pressure within three months that lasted for an entire year.",
      "date_published": "2026-05-11T03:47:24+00:00",
      "authors": [
